Notaulus as tubercle distant from anterolateral margin of mesoscutum ( Figs 34, 35 ). Mesoscutum finely granulate, finely and densely punctate, dorsally almost smooth between punctures. Scutellum with lateral longitudinal carinae extending to posterior c. 0.8 (
Fig. 35
). Foveate groove of mesopleuron situated in anterior 0.6 of mesopleuron, oblique, broad and rather deep, with wrinkles anteriorly usually reaching anterior margin of mesopleuron (
Fig. 34
). Mesopleuron distinctly and densely punctate, smooth and shining between punctures. Propodeum finely granulate, dorsolateral area also finely punctate, with short wrinkles adjacent to all carinae (
Fig. 36
). Propodeum usually with strong basal keel which is 0.31 × as long as apical area (
Fig. 36
); sometimes basal keel indistinct and propodeum dorsally with groove or few longitudinal wrinkles. Propodeal spiracle rather big, separated from pleural carina by 0.5 × diameter of spiracle. Apical area flat, anteriorly usually pointed or narrowly rounded (
Fig. 36
), but sometimes broadly rounded.

Fore wing (
Fig. 4
) with veins Rs + 2 r and Rs angled about 125 °. Vein 2 rs-m almost twice as long as abscissa of M between 2 rs-m and 2 m-cu . Hind wing with cu 1 & cu-a distinctly inclivous. Hind femur 4.45 × as long as broad, 0.83 × as long as tibia.

Head black; face yellowish to reddish brown, always distinctly paler than remaining black head (
Fig. 12
); malar space, clypeus, palpi and mandible (teeth blackish) yellow. Scape and pedicel of antenna brown, ventrally yellowish, flagellum black. Mesosoma brownish orange, propleuron and anterior margin of pronotum yellowish, tegula yellowish to dark brown. Fore and mid legs yellowish orange, tibiae slightly infuscate, fore and sometimes also mid coxae and trochanters whitish. Hind leg with coxa, trochanters and femur brownish orange (sometimes femur brownish), tibia and tarsus brownish, infuscate. Pterostigma and metasomal segment 1 black. Metasoma behind tergite 1 predominantly brownish yellow, tergite 2 and basal half of tergite 3 dorsally dark brown to black, tergites 4 + dorsally usually brownish.
